cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.NI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with synchronization of multi-agent systems, which is a topic in the field of control systems (cs.SY). The use of event-triggered control and communication networks suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The proposed decentralized detection framework and learning-based methods indicate a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the characterization of a Byzantine attack on the system suggests a potential focus on computer security (cs.CR).
